section.section:
"Crime" means an act committed by a person in the State that is:
A crime under Title 1, Subtitle 3, Title 3, Subtitle 7, or § 4-123.1 of the Agriculture Article;
A crime under Title 19, Subtitle 2 or Subtitle 3 of the Business Regulation Article;
A crime under Title 14, Subtitle 29, § 11-810, or § 14-1317 of the Commercial Law Article;
A crime under § 3-218, § 3-305(c)(2), § 3-409(a) or (c), § 3-803(b), § 3-807(i), § 3-808(d), § 3-811(c), § 8-801, § 8-802, § 9-602(e), § 11-702(d)(8), § 11-703(e)(5)(iii), § 11-708(d)(7)(ii), § 11-711(h)(2), § 11-712(c)(6)(ii), § 11-715(g)(2), § 11-716(h)(2), § 11-723(b)(8), or § 11-726 of the Correctional Services Article;
A crime under the Criminal Law Article other than Title 8, Subtitle 2, Part II or § 10-614;
A crime under the Criminal Procedure Article;
A crime under Title 5, Subtitle 10A of the Environment Article;
A crime under § 5-503 of the Family Law Article;
A crime under Title 12, Subtitle 9 of the Financial Institutions Article;
A crime under Title 20, Subtitle 7 or § 21-259.1 of the Health - General Article;
A crime under § 8-713.1, § 8-724.1, § 8-725.5, § 8-725.6, § 8-726.1, § 8-738.1, § 8-740.1, or § 10-411(b), as it relates to Harford County, or (d), as it relates to Anne Arundel County or Caroline County, of the Natural Resources Article;
A crime under Title 3, Subtitle 1 or Subtitle 5, Title 5, Subtitle 1, Subtitle 2, Subtitle 3, or Subtitle 4, § 6-602, § 7-402, or § 12-701 of the Public Safety Article;
A crime under § 14-127 of the Real Property Article;
A violation of the Transportation Article that is punishable by imprisonment;
A crime under Article 2B, Title 22 or § 18-104 of the Code;
A crime under Article 24, § 11-512, § 11-513, or § 11-514 of the Code;
A crime under Chapter 110-1 of the Code of Public Local Laws of Caroline County;
A crime under § 4-103 of the Code of Public Local Laws of Carroll County;
A crime under § 8A-1 of the Code of Public Local Laws of Talbot County; or
A crime at common law.
